contemplating a new design however he said he found the stone 
had been repaired last year by the engraver who was keeping it and 
he agreed to have it restored to its place near the church of st 
thomas the apostle in the village of heptonstall 
the stone bears the name sylvia plath hughes and a line of 
poetry even amidst fierce flames the golden lotus can be 
planted it is a sentence from sanskrit that i used to tell her 
when she was low hughes said 
